
// Connects to a SQLite database specified by the [database] argument, and executes a SQL statement loaded from a file. The [sqlite.connect] slot establishes the connection using the provided database name, while the [sqlite.execute] slot runs the SQL command obtained through [io.file.load], which reads the SQL content from a file.
sqlite.connect:x:@.arguments/*/database
   sqlite.execute:x:@io.file.load
